2ï¸âƒ£ Finding the Maximum of Three Numbers
--------------------------------------------------
Scanner Class for User Input:
- Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in); â†’ Used to take three integer inputs.

Condition Used:
- if (a > b && a > c) â†’ a is the greatest.
- else if (b > c) â†’ b is the greatest.
- else â†’ c is the greatest.

Key Learning:
- The && (AND operator) helps compare multiple conditions.
- The program does not handle equal numbers (can be improved).

Example Cases:
- Input: a = 10, b = 5, c = 8 â†’ Output: 10 is greatest.
- Input: a = 3, b = 7, c = 1 â†’ Output: 7 is greatest.
- Input: a = 6, b = 6, c = 6 â†’ Output: 6 is greatest.

Closing the Scanner:
- sc.close(); â†’ Closes the scanner to avoid memory leaks.

