3ï¸âƒ£ Checking if a Number is Even or Odd
--------------------------------------------------
Scanner Class for User Input:
- Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in); â†’ Takes an integer input.

Condition Used:
- if (num % 2 == 0) â†’ The number is Even.
- else â†’ The number is Odd.

Key Learning:
- The % (modulus operator) helps check divisibility by 2.

Edge Cases:
- Negative numbers also follow the same rule.
- 0 is even because 0 % 2 == 0.

Example Cases:
- Input: 8 â†’ Output: Even.
- Input: 13 â†’ Output: Odd.
- Input: -4 â†’ Output: Even.

Closing the Scanner:
- sc.close(); â†’ Closes the scanner to avoid memory leaks.

