6ï¸âƒ£ Identifying the Radix (Base) of a Number
--------------------------------------------------
Scanner Class for User Input:
- Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in); â†’ Takes a string input for number checking.

Condition Used (Regex Matching):
- [01]+ â†’ Binary (Base 2) â†’ Digits allowed: 0, 1.
- [0-7]+ â†’ Octal (Base 8) â†’ Digits allowed: 0-7.
- [0-9]+ â†’ Decimal (Base 10) â†’ Digits allowed: 0-9.
- [0-9A-Fa-f]+ â†’ Hexadecimal (Base 16) â†’ Digits: 0-9, A-F/a-f.

Key Learning:
- Regex (matches()) is useful for pattern-based conditions.
- Different numbering systems follow specific digit constraints.

Example Cases:
- Input: "1010" â†’ Output: Binary.
- Input: "745" â†’ Output: Octal.
- Input: "9876" â†’ Output: Decimal.
- Input: "A1B3" â†’ Output: Hexadecimal.

Closing the Scanner:
- sc.close(); â†’ Closes the scanner to avoid memory leaks.

